{
  "texts": [
    "The CNN-LSTM model has two outputs: (i) DIR total population and (ii) DIR 0-19.",
    "Dimensionality reduction In order to simplify the number of variables and types, Partial Least Square (PLS) was applied to the dataset, after the normalisation step, as a dimensionality reduction strategy.",
    "By using PLS, the dimension V of the dataset was reduced to V * (e.g.",
    "starting from a set of N = 100 samples, where each sample is a collection of V = 10 variables, after applying the PLS, by setting the number of output components equals to 4, the set is transformed in a new set containing N = 100 samples, where each sample is a collection of V * = 4 components).",
    "The number of PLS components for each group of variables is 4 for the Climatic group, 6 for the Geophysical one and 10 for the Socio-economical one."
  ]
}